OL,3,CPensioner's sentence upped for
OL,4,Ctrafficking addicted women into
OL,5,Cprostitution
OL,7,FThe former car salesman was told he
OL,8,Fmust now serve a nine-year sentence
OL,9,Ffor a campaign of exploitation
OL,10,Fdescribed as the most serious of its
OL,11,Fkind in Northern Ireland.
OL,13,FLady Chief Justice Dame Siobhan Keegan
OL,14,Fsaid: "He portrayed himself as some
OL,15,Fsort of saviour, rather than a
OL,16,Fcalculated abuser of vulnerable young
OL,17,Fwomen."
