OL,4,Ctrafficking addicted women into
OL,5,Cprostitution
OL,7,FWith some of the women suffering from
OL,8,Faddiction, homelessness or mental
OL,9,Fhealth issues, MacCormack drove them
OL,10,Fto meet customers even if they were
OL,11,Fhigh on drugs or in a state of
OL,12,Fwithdrawal.
OL,14,FThree other men were also convicted of
OL,15,Frelated crimes following a major
OL,16,Finvestigation by the PSNI's modern
OL,17,Fslavery and human trafficking unit.
