OL,4,Ctrafficking addicted women into
OL,5,Cprostitution
OL,7,FEarlier this year MacCormack received
OL,8,Fa seven-year term at Belfast Crown
OL,9,FCourt, with half to be served behind
OL,10,Fbars and half on licence.
OL,12,FBased on the period already spent on
OL,13,Fremand, he was due to be released by
OL,14,FNovember.
OL,16,FBut the Public Prosecution Service
OL,17,Fchallenged the sentence, claiming it
OL,18,Fwas unduly lenient by failing to fully
OL,19,Freflect the high culpability,
OL,20,Faggravating features and need for
OL,21,Fdeterrence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
