OL,4,Ctrafficking addicted women into
OL,5,Cprostitution
OL,7,F"This was a case involving a suite of
OL,8,Foffending against vulnerable women
OL,9,Fwhich requires appropriate punishment
OL,10,Fto deter this type of behaviour in our
OL,11,Fcommunity and to soundly rebut the
OL,12,Fattitude of the defendant. Such
OL,13,Fattitudes have no place in our
OL,14,Fsociety," the Lady Chief Justice
OL,15,Fstated.
OL,17,FShe confirmed: "We will replace the
OL,18,Fsentence of seven years originally
OL,19,Fimposed for one of nine years, split
OL,20,Fequally between custody and licence."
